Preconditions:
- The input array `nums` is not null.
- The input array `nums` has at least two elements.
- The input integer `k` is not null.

Postconditions:
- The method returns an integer value representing the number of pairs `(i, j)` where `i < j` and `|nums[i] - nums[j]| == k`.
- The method does not modify the input array `nums`.
- The method does not modify the input integer `k`.